plt.figure(figsize=(14, 8))
for ticker in returns.columns:
    plt.plot(returns[ticker].cumsum(), label=ticker)
plt.title('Stock Cumulative Returns of Top Companies')
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.ylabel('Cumulative Returns')
plt.legend()
plt.show()
In [9]:
from __visualization.colors import colors_fader, colormap

colors = colors_fader(color1 = "#0064d2", color2 = "#e53238", number = 10)
cmap = colormap(colors)

# Calculate the correlation matrix
correlation_matrix = returns.corr()

# Create a heatmap of the correlations using the custom color map
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
seaborn.heatmap(
    correlation_matrix, 
    vmin=-1,
    vmax=1,
    annot=True, 
    fmt=".2f", 
    cmap=cmap, 
    square=True, 
    cbar_kws={"shrink": .8, "ticks": np.linspace(-1, 1, 10+1)}  # Ensure cbar shows -1.0
)
plt.title('Heatmap of Stock Returns Correlations')
plt.show()
